          furniture-grade custom bathroom vanities</strong> with
          <a href="/services/granite-countertops" class="text-yellow-600 font-bold hover:underline">granite and quartz countertops</a>,
          creating moisture-resistant sanctuaries that last a lifetime.
          Call <a href="tel:9519731265" class="text-yellow-600 font-bold hover:underline">{phone}</a> for a free consultation.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-16 mb-24">
        <div class="lg:col-span-8 space-y-8 text-lg text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">

          <section class="reveal">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">Custom Bathroom Vanities — Built by the Source</h2>
            <p>
              When homeowners search for <strong>"bathroom remodeling near me"</strong> in the Temecula Valley,
              they often find general contractors who outsource their cabinets. At <a href="/" class="text-yellow-600 font-bold hover:underline">First Class WoodWorks</a>,
              we are the source. As licensed, bonded, and insured
              <a href="/services/cabinet-maker" class="text-yellow-600 font-bold hover:underline">cabinet makers</a>,
              we build every vanity in-house to your exact specifications.
            </p>
            <p>
              From the luxury estates in <strong>Bear Creek</strong> to the custom homes of <strong>La Cresta</strong>,
              we specialize in high-end bathroom transformations. Our process includes full 3D design renderings,
              allowing you to see your floating vanity or double-sink master unit before we cut the first piece of wood.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="bg-zinc-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-600 p-8 my-10 reveal">
            <h4 class="text-zinc-900 font-bold mb-2">Master Cabinet Maker Pro-Tip:</h4>
            <p class="italic">"In Murrieta's dry climate, we use a post-catalyzed conversion varnish on all bathroom cabinetry. This creates a chemical-resistant and moisture-proof barrier that prevents the wood checking and finish cracks common in mass-produced vanities. It's the same professional coating used on commercial-grade furniture."</p>
          </div>

          <section class="reveal">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">What We Build for Your Bathroom</h2>
            <p>
              Every bathroom project is designed, built, and installed by our own team.
              Here's what we provide:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 mt-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span>
                <span><strong>Custom Floating Vanities</strong> — Wall-mounted designs with reinforced French cleats and structural blocking. Creates a modern, open feel and makes floor cleaning effortless.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span>
                <span><strong><a href="/services/granite-countertops" class="text-yellow-600 hover:underline">Granite & Quartz Vanity Tops</a></strong> — Hand-selected natural stone and engineered surfaces, precision-templated after vanity installation for a seamless fit.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span>
                <span><strong>Double-Sink Master Vanities</strong> — His-and-hers configurations with custom drawer organizers, Blum soft-close slides, and integrated electrical outlets.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span>
                <span><strong>Linen Tower Built-Ins</strong> — Floor-to-ceiling storage towers that match your vanity, eliminating the need for freestanding bathroom furniture.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span>
                <span><strong>Furniture-Grade Medicine Cabinets</strong> — Recessed or surface-mounted, built from the same hardwoods as your vanity with soft-close hinges and adjustable shelving.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span>
                <span><strong>Makeup Vanity Stations</strong> — Custom seated vanities with dedicated lighting, drawer organizers, and countertop space built into your master suite design.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="reveal bg-zinc-50 p-8 rounded-sm border border-zinc-100">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-6 text-center">Custom Vanity vs. Big-Box Bathroom Vanity</h3>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
              <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
                <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200">
                  <tr>
                    <th class="pb-4 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-600">Feature</th>
                    <th class="pb-4 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-400">Big-Box Vanity</th>
                    <th class="pb-4 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-yellow-600">First Class Custom Vanity</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-200">
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Materials</td><td class="py-4 text-zinc-500">MDF / particle board</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Furniture-grade plywood & hardwoods</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Moisture Protection</td><td class="py-4 text-zinc-500">Painted surface (peels in 2-3 years)</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Conversion varnish (moisture-proof)</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Sizing</td><td class="py-4 text-zinc-500">Standard sizes (24", 30", 36")</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Built to your exact dimensions</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Countertop</td><td class="py-4 text-zinc-500">Cultured marble or laminate</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Real granite, quartz, or marble</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Hardware</td><td class="py-4 text-zinc-500">Plastic drawer slides</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Blum soft-close (lifetime warranty)</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Lifespan</td><td class="py-4 text-zinc-500">3-5 years in a humid bathroom</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Lifetime — built to outlast the home</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="reveal">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">Granite & Stone Vanity Tops</h2>
            <p>
              Every custom vanity we build pairs beautifully with a
              <a href="/services/granite-countertops" class="text-yellow-600 font-bold hover:underline">natural stone or quartz countertop</a>.
              We coordinate the entire process — slab selection, templating after vanity installation,
              fabrication, and final installation — so your vanity and countertop work as one integrated piece.
            </p>
            <p>
              For master bathrooms, we recommend granite or quartzite for their heat resistance and unique
              natural veining. For powder rooms and guest baths, quartz offers a maintenance-free option
              with consistent coloring that complements any design style.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="reveal">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">Our Bathroom Remodeling Process</h2>
            <div class="space-y-6 mt-6">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-serif text-2xl font-bold">1.</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-zinc-900">In-Home Consultation & Measurement</p>
                  <p>We visit your Murrieta, Temecula, or Menifee home, assess the existing bathroom, take laser measurements, and discuss your design vision, storage needs, and budget.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-serif text-2xl font-bold">2.</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-zinc-900">3D Design & Material Selection</p>
                  <p>You see your new bathroom in full 3D renderings. We select wood species, stain colors, countertop materials, and hardware finishes together. You approve every detail before we start.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-serif text-2xl font-bold">3.</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-zinc-900">In-Shop Vanity Fabrication</p>
                  <p>Your vanity is built by our craftsmen using dovetailed drawers, mortise-and-tenon face frames, and conversion varnish — cured in controlled shop conditions for maximum moisture resistance.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="text-yellow-600 font-serif text-2xl font-bold">4.</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-zinc-900">Installation & Countertop Coordination</p>
                  <p>The vanity is installed, then the <a href="/services/granite-countertops" class="text-yellow-600 hover:underline">countertop</a> is templated and fabricated for a precision fit. Plumbing, backsplash, and finish details are coordinated as one project.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="reveal">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 pt-10 mb-6">Bathroom Remodeling FAQ</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
              {faqs.map((faq) => (
                <details class="group bg-zinc-50 border border-zinc-200 rounded-sm hover:shadow-md transition-all">
                  <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-6 list-none">
                    <h4 class="font-serif font-bold text-zinc-800 group-hover:text-yellow-600 transition-colors pr-8">
                      {faq.question}
                    </h4>
                    <span class="text-yellow-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0">
                      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" class="w-5 h-5">
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
                      </svg>
                    </span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed text-base border-t border-zinc-100 pt-4">
                    {faq.answer}
                  </div>
                </details>
              ))}
            </div>
          </section>

        </div>

        <aside class="lg:col-span-4 space-y-8 sticky top-32">
          <div class="bg-zinc-900 text-white p-10 rounded-sm reveal">
            <h3 class="font-serif font-bold text-2xl mb-2 text-yellow-600">Master Bath Services</h3>
            <p class="text-zinc-500 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] font-bold mb-6">Murrieta, CA &bull; 5.0 Star Rated</p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-white/80 text-sm mb-8">
              <li class="border-b border-white/10 pb-3">Custom Floating Vanities</li>
              <li class="border-b border-white/10 pb-3">Granite & Quartz Vanity Tops</li>
              <li class="border-b border-white/10 pb-3">Double-Sink Master Vanities</li>
              <li class="border-b border-white/10 pb-3">Linen Tower Built-Ins</li>
              <li class="border-b border-white/10 pb-3">Furniture-Grade Medicine Cabinets</li>
              <li class="border-b border-white/10 pb-3">Makeup Vanity Stations</li>
              <li class="border-b border-white/10 pb-3">Moisture-Proof Finishing</li>
              <li>A+ BBB Accredited &bull; Licensed &amp; Bonded</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="tel:9519731265" class="block text-center border border-yellow-600 py-4 font-bold hover:bg-yellow-600 hover:text-zinc-900 transition mb-3">
              {phone}
            </a>
            <a href="/contact" class="block text-center bg-yellow-600 text-zinc-900 py-4 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs hover:bg-yellow-700 transition">
              Start My Bathroom Quote
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-zinc-50 border border-zinc-200 p-8 rounded-sm reveal">
            <h3 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-zinc-500 mb-6">Related Services</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-zinc-600">
              <li><a href="/services/granite-countertops" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition font-bold">Granite Countertops</a></li>
              <li><a href="/services/custom-kitchen-cabinets" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition">Custom Kitchen Cabinets</a></li>
              <li><a href="/services/kitchen-remodeling" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition">Kitchen Remodeling</a></li>
              <li><a href="/services/cabinet-maker" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition">Cabinet Maker</a></li>
              <li><a href="/services/custom-woodworking" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition">Custom Woodworking</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-zinc-50 border border-zinc-200 p-8 rounded-sm reveal">
            <h3 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-zinc-500 mb-6">Areas We Serve</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-zinc-600">
              <li><a href="/cities/murrieta" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition font-bold">Murrieta (HQ)</a></li>
              <li><a href="/cities/temecula" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition">Temecula</a></li>
              <li><a href="/cities/menifee" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition">Menifee</a></li>
              <li><a href="/cities/wildomar" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition">Wildomar</a></li>
              <li><a href="/cities/fallbrook" class="hover:text-yellow-600 transition">Fallbrook</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

  <section class="border-t border-zinc-100 pt-20 pb-20 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
    <Services />
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  details > summary { list-style: none; }
  details > summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .reveal { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); transition: all 0.8s ease-out; }
  .reveal.active { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
</style>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) entry.target.classList.add('active');
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.1 });
  document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
</script>
